The paper deals with channel estimation in massive MIMO-OFDM systems, which involves signal processing, wireless communication, and network information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves distributed algorithms and collaboration among neighboring antenna elements, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of stochastic geometry to obtain analytical expressions for interference variance and power suggests the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with the use of large antenna arrays, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of pilot contamination, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
